            "answer_text": "I think it was a fantastic deal,   not only did it bring some money to the coffers it achieve 2 long term strategic goals no amount of money could buy. It denied a trove of ressources to the competing superpower who was anyway poised to confiscate it.It ensured that this trove of ressources went to our closest ally, setting the USA to become a friendly superpower (later hyperpower).  We got infinitely more value from Louisiana as part of the US than if we had kept it (and if we had kept it how long would we have kept it? see Christophe Schermesser's answer ). ",
